{
  "title": "Data tables",
  "href": "http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/data-tables.html",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "<p>Data tables are used to present raw data sets, and usually appear in desktop enterprise products.</p><p>Data sets may include:</p><ul><li>Three or more columns of data</li><li>A corresponding visualization</li><li>The ability for users to query and manipulate data at scale</li></ul>"
    },
    {
      "type": "article-list",
      "articles": [
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Structure",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>In its simplest form, a data table contains a top row of column names, and rows for data. Checkboxes should accompany each row if the user needs to select or manipulate data.</p>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhV25CdGNXYzA4cXM/components_datatables_structure_basictable.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Basic data table</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Column headers</strong></p><ul><li>12sp Roboto Medium</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Table content</strong></p><ul><li>13sp Roboto Regular</li><li>87% black</li></ul>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Text alignment</strong></p><ul><li>Right-align numeric columns</li><li>Left-align text columns</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Interaction",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Display a background fill when the user hovers over any part of a row. If there are separate hover states on individual (e.g. editable) cells, display both the hover state of the cell and row at the same time.</p><p><strong>Hover background</strong></p><ul><li>Grey 200 (#EEEEEE)</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhUDEyWVZTVDJCMHM/components_datatables_interaction_rowhover.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Hovering over a row</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Row hover (Desktop)"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>When a row is selected, use a background fill on the row. </p><p><strong>Selected row background</strong></p><ul><li>Grey 100 (#F5F5F5)</li></ul><p><strong>Checkbox</strong></p><ul><li>Use secondary app color</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhcWNyQl9xYmRkQnc/components_datatables_interaction_selectedrow.png",
                      "caption": "<p>A selected table row</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Row selection"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>If column sorting is enabled, sort the most important data by default and display a sorted state in the column header. If the user clicks on a column that is already sorted, reverse the sort order and rotate the sort icon.</p><p><strong>Sorted column name</strong></p><ul><li>12sp Roboto Medium</li><li>87% black</li></ul><p><strong>Sort icon</strong></p><ul><li>16dp container</li><li>87% black</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhMW1haUJDRWJKLUk/components_datatables_interaction_sortedcolumn.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Table with an ascending sorted column</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Sorted column"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>If there is a need to provide definitions to column headers, display a tooltip on hover. If sorting is enabled, display a light sort icon upon hover, which indicates that the column is sortable. </p><p><strong>Tooltip</strong></p><ul><li>Follow the guidelines for <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/tooltips.html\">Tooltips</a></li></ul><p><strong>Sort icon</strong></p><ul><li>16dp container</li><li>26% black</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhenh5SWhFdFlyajg/components_datatables_interaction_tooltip.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Hovering over a column name</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Column name hover (Desktop)"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Sometimes, column names don&#x2019;t fit in a container with the recommended 56dp of padding in between columns. There are two options to handle this:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li>Display the full column name and enable horizontal scrolling in the table container.</li><li>Shorten the column name and display it in full on hover.</li></ol>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhMkVuNC1Zd3QyZ1k/components_datatables_interaction_longtitle1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Long column names truncated with an ellipse</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhclI1SGllZkZQTkE/components_datatables_interaction_longtitle2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Hovering over a truncated column name</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Long header titles"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Tables may require basic text editing (e.g. for editing existing text content, or adding comments). Include editable fields within a table and denote them using placeholder text. You can use a simple edit dialog with just a text field, or display a full dialog component on click. </p><p><strong>Placeholder text</strong></p><ul><li>13sp Roboto Regular</li><li>26% black</li><li>No divider line on text field</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhZTViOVFXZTNucGs/components_datatables_interaction_editing1.png"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Inline text editing"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Small edit dialog</strong></p><ul><li>Align edges of dialog with nearest divider lines, or table edges</li><li>24dp of left and right padding</li><li>Include a single <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/text-fields.html\">text field</a>, applying the app theme where applicable</li><li>User confirms text by pressing Enter</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhZHhJSVhoT2JuTkE/components_datatables_interaction_editing2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>A simple, one-field edit dialog</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Large edit dialog</strong></p><ul><li>Align edges of dialog with nearest divider lines, or table edges</li><li>Follow the <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/dialogs.html\">dialog</a> guidelines, applying the app theme where applicable</li><li>User confirms text by clicking the Save button</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhZkY4b1VkME5QcXM/components_datatables_interaction_editing3.png",
                      "caption": "<p>A complex, flexible edit dialog</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Inline edit icon</strong></p><ul><li>18dp container</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhazJZa2VmSU5ldTQ/components_datatables_interaction_editing4.png",
                      "caption": "<p>(Optional) Icon-based edit affordance. Include icons at the edge of the cell on the opposite side of the content. </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Instead of editing text, users may need to select from a predefined list of options. In this scenario, embed a menu component directly in the table.</p><p><strong>Inline menu</strong></p><ul><li>13sp Roboto Regular</li><li>87% black</li><li>Follow spacing and sizing guidelines for <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/components/menus.html\">menus</a></li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhblJlanhBSHYzNWs/components_datatables_interaction_inlinemenus1.png",
                      "caption": "<p>A table with inline menus</p>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhV200T3NSWG9TZFU/components_datatables_interaction_inlinemenus2.png",
                      "caption": "<p>An expanded inline menu</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "title": "Inline menus"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Tables within cards",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Tables can be embedded within a card, with table navigation and data manipulation tools available at the top and bottom.</p>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhUTEwa21JUEtza0k/components_datatables_cards_tablecard.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Table card with header and footer</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Card title</strong></p><ul><li>20sp Roboto Regular</li><li>87% black</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Card action icons (header and footer)</strong></p><ul><li>24dp container</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Footer pagination labels </strong></p><ul><li>12sp Roboto Regular</li><li>54% black</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Some table cards may require headers with actions instead of titles. Two possible approaches to this are to display persistent actions, or a contextual header that activates when items are selected.</p>"
                }
              ],
              "title": "Alternate headers"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhemNvbnZOcXNpODQ/components_datatables_cards_altheaders.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Alternate headers for a table card</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Action buttons</strong></p><ul><li>Use borderless buttons</li><li>Enable upon item selection</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "text",
                      "src": "<p><strong>Colored header</strong></p><ul><li>Use 50-value of secondary app color for background fill</li><li>Display the number of items selected</li><li>Display available contextual icons upon item selection</li></ul>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "Specs",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                }
              ],
              "title": "Vertical spacing"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhNEs2bWtmUDdPWWc/components_datatables_specs_verticalspacing.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Vertical spacing of a data table card and its last row</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<ol start=\"1\"><li>64dp card header height</li><li>56dp height for last row</li><li>48dp data row height</li></ol>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                }
              ],
              "title": "Header & footer padding"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhTV91bEF3cWl5eG8/components_datatables_specs_01_horizontalspacing.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Horizontal padding between elements in a table card</p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<ol start=\"1\"><li>24dp of padding around the perimeter of table cards</li><li>32dp in between footer control sets</li><li>40dp in between the footer row count and its label</li></ol>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": ""
                }
              ],
              "title": "Column padding"
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
                      "src": "media/publish/material_v_4/material_ext_publish/0B3mOPoJlxiFhckNvQzhHaWI5Ulk/components_datatables_specs_02_horizontalspacing.png",
                      "caption": "<p>Padding in between columns </p>"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<ol start=\"1\"><li>Use a minimum of 56dp of padding in between columns. The widest item in the column (including data and column name) should delineate the column border. </li><li>Checkbox icons have a width and height of 18dp within a 24dp icon container.</li></ol>"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
